{"word":"φίλιος","slug":"φίλιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φίλιος</b></el> <el>(φίλιος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φίλος'><el>φίλος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>of</i> or <i>from a friend, friendly</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>φ. τριήρης</el> <i>a friendly</i> ship, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; <el>ἡ φιλία</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> <el>γῆ, χώρα</el>) <i>a friendly country</i>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>ἡ πολεμία</el>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>Ζεὺς φίλιος</el> Zeus <i>as god of friendship</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>ναὶ τὸν φίλιον</el> (<a href='S:subaudi, subaudito'>sub.</a> <el>Δία</el>) <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>πρὸς φιλίου</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a>, <i>beloved, dear</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-ίως</el>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}